piders in upper guk no contest.<br>
<br>
there are 14 spiders total if memory serves. while crag spiders may drop silks more frequently there are 2 reasons why heart spiders are 100 times better than crag spiders<br>
<br>
1. its a camp - dont need to run around trying to be first to a roamer - dont have to worry about killing mobs on the same spawn table to keep the spawn rotating - you are guaranteed 14 spiders every 15ish minutes.<br>
<br>
2. its a safe camp - sit far back enough in the first &quot;alcove&quot; (where the giant spider spawns) and nothing will aggro you. This means you can go afk between spawns if you want without fear that youll get jumped. Lets face it, farming silk is a seriously boring proposition - you may as well not let that stop you from watching something on TV or doing something else while you wait.<br>
<br>
you can clear all 14 spawns in 3 fights - 10 spawns upstairs, 4 spawns on the &quot;bridge&quot; area - above the water where the skeletal monk for acumen mask spawns.<br>
<br>
IMO anyone who would say that EK is best is trying to keep upper guk a &quot;secret&quot;. Dont be mislead - EK is only better if you have sow and tracking and can stand the tedium of doing something mundane over and over and over again. <p><font face="verdana" size="2">[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=85843" target="new"><b>Diomedes</b></a></font> (High Elf) <font face="verdana" size="2">
<font face="verdana" size="2">&lt;The Vagrants&gt; ZONE:ezboard</font><br><b>
<font face="verdana" size="2">The Tribunal</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/01 8:59:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_thumb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> Yes, but you have to admit it's fun to PBAoE the gnolls by the ramp to Highpass every 10 minutes or so when you're in EK.  I haven't checked, but I may actually not be KoS to the Karana bandits anymore.  Plus you get scalps you can turn in in Highpass for several good factions, including Freeport Militia, if I recall correctly.  I might be thinking of Highkeep goblin ears though.<br>
