</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fredre>Fredre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 8:52:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I would have to say EK.  While it does sound like Guk would be better (haven't been there myself), I prefer EK several additional reasons.  One, there are a bunch of lions running around and the HQ pelts can get you to 115 with quivers and the ruined ones can be used to make poison vials (+ pearl + 'chanter friend + silk) can make Wu's armor which get into the upper 140's, IIRC.  Two, there are the occasional HG's that wander about which are good for XP (well at least for me) and cash.  Occasionally you have to clean out the crawlers and hounds, since the number of them seems inversely proportional to the number of lions and spiders.<br>
