Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usbrobin24.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sbrobin24</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 7:08:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> &quot;heart spiders in upper guk no contest.&quot;<br>
<br>
I contest.   I tried EK at level 50. I tried guk at 50.  Didn't have enough mana to kill all the spiders in guk until I got that static pulse spell.  I took my 45 necro to EK and there are MUCH more spiders. Sure, you have to run around, but you can get many more silks.   14 spiders every 18 mins is less than the 18 crags I can kill in EK in 18 mins, especially since crags drop more silk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/6/01 10:55:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I should add that in EK, if you kill snakes as well as spiders, you'll get more spiders to spawn. They seem to be on the same spawn table.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>
Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualurarz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alura RZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/8/01 1:15:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Using 2 computers, I had a wizard camping at EK, and I had a warrior camped at l guk killing all heart spider spawns.  I'm not sure how long the time was but I reached 8 stacks of spider silk in EK before I reached 6 stacks in l guk, even though 1) I didn't kill all the available spiders in EK, 2) think this is statistically significant.  <br>
<br>
EK Crag spiders just drop alot of spider silks  thank heart spiders.  Of course this changes if there is a druid camping spiders too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyaldin111.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaldin111</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/24/01 1:48:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Lguk deadly black widows, low 20's spiders, generally get 2 silks off of em but its a linear camp, they're not hard and there's lots of em and it's hardly ever camped.  Got a ton of silks this way.<br>
